{"lemma":"شَمالُ","slug":"شَمالُ","root":"ش.م.ل","root_slug":"ش-م-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-م-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَمالُ","root":"شمل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23051","n23052","n23053"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"left hand"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"left side"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bad omen"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"handful of ears"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"case, sheath, wrapping"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"north"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"north wind"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *śimaʔl-. Cognate with Hebrew שְׂמֹאל (s'mól, “left”), Akkadian 𒆏 (šumēlum, “left side”), Aramaic סְמָלָא (səmālā) / ܣܡܠܐ (semmālā, “left side”), Ugaritic 𐎌𐎎𐎀𐎍 (šmảl). The north sense derives from the left-hand side facing the sunrise, also attested in Sabaean 𐩠𐩦𐩱𐩣𐩡 (hs²ʾml, “to be northward”).\n\nFrom the root ش م ل (š m l) meaning “to bundle, “to wrap”, “to huddle”, “to be cold” – such senses are influenced by the cold-dry northerly wind necessitating wrapping up with clothes.\n\nFrom the root ش م ل (š m l) meaning “to be leftward” – the north direction being the left-hand side facing the sunrise; constrast with اَلْيَمَن (al-yaman), originally denoting one's right-hand side, before developing the sense of \"the south\". Additionally it is relatable to the root meaning “to bundle” or “to wrap”, as the cold northern wind necessitated wrapping up with clothes, contrasting with جَنُوب (janūb, “south”) from the root ج ن ب (j n b) meaning “changing”, “laying aside” clothes, the warm southern wind allowing to put off clothes."},"ipa":["/ʃi.maːl/","/ʃa.maːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23051","headword_ar":"شَمَالٌ","root":"$ml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, &c.,) the most common form of the word, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAlN","text_ar":"شِمَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [a form which I think objectionable as likely to cause confusion, though it is probably the original form,] (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amoA^alN","text_ar":"شَمْاَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amoA^al~N","text_ar":"شَمْاَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, [in one place in the O erroneously written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA^mal~","text_ar":"شَامَلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA^omalN","text_ar":"شَاْمَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) which last is formed by transposition, (S, O, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAmalN","text_ar":"شَامَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awomalN","text_ar":"شَوْمَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayomalN","text_ar":"شَيْمَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amuwlN","text_ar":"شَمُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amiylN","text_ar":"شَمِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amalN","text_ar":"شَمَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amolN","text_ar":"شَمْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the last said by ISd not to have been heard except in the poetry of El-Ba'eeth, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amal~N","text_ar":"شَمَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,) [every one of these] used as a subst. and as an epithet, (K,) [so that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHu Al$~amaAli","text_ar":"رِيحُ الشَّمَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN $amaAlN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ شَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAlN","text_ar":"شَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. alone; The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"north wind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a northerly wind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that is the opposite to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"januwb","text_ar":"جَنُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that blows from the direction of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quTob","text_ar":"قُطْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pole-star"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that blows from the direction of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hijor","text_ar":"حِجْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is on what is called the north, but what is rather to be called the north-west, side of the Kaabeh]: (M, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that blows from the direction of the right hand of a person facing the Kibleh"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by which is meant the angle of the Black Stone; i. e., correctly speaking,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the north"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Th, M, K:) or, correctly, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that blows from between the place of sunrise and the constellation of the Bear"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAt naEo$","text_ar":"بَنَات نَعْش"},{"kind":"text","text":"): or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from between the place of sunrise and the place of setting of the constellation of the Eagle"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asor","text_ar":"النَّسْر"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1601},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aAy^ir","text_ar":"الطَّايِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (IAar, K:) [i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that blows from some point of the north-east quarter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearly so:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it was probably thus named as being the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that blows from the direction of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAl","text_ar":"شِمَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left side"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a person facing the rising sun;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"north wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a northerly wind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] it seldom, or never, blows in the night: (K:) when it blows for seven days upon the people of Egypt, they prepare the graveclothes, for its nature is deadly: it is cold and dry: (TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakobaA='u","text_ar":"نَكْبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAlN","text_ar":"شَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAlaAtN","text_ar":"شَمَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAy^ilu","text_ar":"شَمَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is anomalous, as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAlapN","text_ar":"شَمَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^a$aAmil","text_ar":"الاَشَامِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"also occurs, coupled with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ajaAnib","text_ar":"الاَجَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a verse of Et- Tirimmáh; and [as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajaAnibu","text_ar":"اَجَانِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a reg. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonubN","text_ar":"اَجْنُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"januwbN","text_ar":"جَنُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] ISd thinks that they formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amolN","text_ar":"شَمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$omalN","text_ar":"اَشْمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and then from this last, the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAmilu","text_ar":"اَشَامِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSabotu mino fulaAnK $amalFA","text_ar":"اَصَبْتُ مِنْ فُلَانٍ شَمَلًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHFA","text_ar":"رِيحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I perceived from such a one an odour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a foul odour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","O","MF","TA","M","Th","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n23052","headword_ar":"شِمَالٌ","root":"$ml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, &c.,) applied to one of the hands or arms, (S, Msb,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiynN","text_ar":"يَمِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iymaAlN","text_ar":"شِيمَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amAl","text_ar":"الشَّمال"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~mAl","text_ar":"الشّمال"},{"kind":"text","text":"are erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~imaAl","text_ar":"الشِّمَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iymaAl","text_ar":"الشِّيمَال"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) the latter thought by ISd to be used only by poetic license, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAlN","text_ar":"شِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imolaAlN","text_ar":"شِمْلَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AA, S, O, K,) this last not known to Ks nor to As: (TA:) of the fem. gender: (S, O, Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$omulN","text_ar":"اَشْمُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) because it is fem., (S, O,) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAy^ilu","text_ar":"شَمَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) which is anomalous, (S, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$umulN","text_ar":"شُمُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAlN","text_ar":"شِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the sing. (K.) ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the hand so called:"},{"kind":"text","text":"you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ailotafata yamiynFA wa$imaAlFA","text_ar":"اِلْتَفَتَ يَمِينًا وَشِمَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned his face,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the direction of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ymyn","text_ar":"يمين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in the direction of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$mAl","text_ar":"شمال"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. in this sense also is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^u$omulN","text_ar":"اُشْمُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAy^ilu","text_ar":"شَمَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba A_ilaY A^ayomuni AlA_ibili waA^a$omulihaA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ اـِلَى اَيْمُنِ الاـِبِلِ وَاَشْمُلِهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went to the right sides of the camels and the left sides thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ymn","text_ar":"يمن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  [Hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ill luck, unluckiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tayoru","text_ar":"طَيْرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~imaAli","text_ar":"الشِّمَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Birds of ill luck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every bird from which one augurs evil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY lahu guraAbu $imaAlK","text_ar":"جَرَى لَهُ غُرَابُ شِمَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What was disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated, happened to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the bird [to which this is likened] came to him from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAl","text_ar":"شِمَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or direction of the left hand]. (TA.) And when the place that a person occupies is rendered evil, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN EinodiY","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ عِنْدِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAl$~imaAli","text_ar":"بِالشِّمَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is with me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in my estimation, in an evil plight"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAlN","text_ar":"شَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every handful of corn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seedproduce, which the reaper grasps"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. because grasped with his left hand]. (K.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort of bag that is put upon the udder of the ewe"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the udder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is heavy"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, * TA:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peculiar to the she-goat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$umulN","text_ar":"شُمُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraAbapN","text_ar":"عَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A similar thing that is put to the raceme of a palm-tree, made with pieces of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the garments called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akosiyap","text_ar":"اَكْسِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='N","text_ar":"كِسَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that the fruit may not be shaken off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) [In this sense it may perhaps be from the same word as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amolapN","text_ar":"شَمْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark made with a hot iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simapN","text_ar":"سِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the udder of a ewe"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A nature;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a natural disposition"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temper"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, K:) accord. to Er-Rághib, so called because [it is as though it were a thing] inwrapping the man [and restricting his freedom of action], like as the [garments called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAl","text_ar":"شِمَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amolapN","text_ar":"شَمْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] inwrap the body: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAy^ilu","text_ar":"شَمَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAlN","text_ar":"شِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, [which seems to be rarely used as a sing. in this sense,] may be a pl., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dilaASN","text_ar":"دِلَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA; and Ham p. 489, q. v.) 'Abd-Yaghooth El-Hárithee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^alamo taEolamaA A^an~a AlmalaAmapa nafoEuhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        qaliylN wamaA lawomiY A^axiYmino $imaAliyaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Know not ye two that the utility of censure is little, and my censuring my brother is not of my nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of my natural dispositions?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, TA:) here it may be a pl., of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijaAnN","text_ar":"هِجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dilaASN","text_ar":"دِلَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or it may be ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAliyaA","text_ar":"شَمَالِيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] an instance of transposition, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAy^iliY","text_ar":"شَمَايِلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imil~N","text_ar":"شِمِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","AA","O","K","A"]},{"entry_id":"n23053","headword_ar":"شَمْاَلٌ","root":"$ml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amoA^al~N","text_ar":"شَمْاَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAlN","text_ar":"شَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}